Visakhapatnam is on Kolkata-Chennai main line and is connected to several cities of the country by rail. All trains including fast expresses stop at the station. Visakhapatnam station comes under the East Coast Railways zone and is one of the principal Divisional Headquarters (under the British name Waltair). It has eight platforms, the first in East Coast railways to have this many, and all of them can accommodate trains with up to 28 coaches.

